    <table cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" border="0" width="100%">
    <tr>
        <td id="descriptionArea">
            <ul>
	<li><b>User Story:</b> <em>As a Security Tester, I want to ensure the system rejects files over the size limit so that our storage and server performance are protected.</em></li>
	<li><b>Technical Scope:</b> Use Postman or a script to attempt uploading a file larger than the 5MB/10MB limits defined by Min Khant.</li>
	<li><b>Acceptance Criteria:</b> The server correctly returns a $413\text
{ Payload Too Large}
<p>$ or a custom error message, and the frontend handles it without crashing.</p></li>
</ul>

            <br/>
        </td>
    </tr>
    </table>

