    <table cellpadding="2" cellspacing="0" border="0" width="100%" align="center">
    <tr>
        <td bgcolor="#bbbbbb" width="1%" nowrap align="center">
            &nbsp;<font color="#ffffff"><b>Description</b></font>&nbsp;
        </td>
        <td>&nbsp;</td>
    </tr>
    </table>

    <table cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" border="0" width="100%">
    <tr>
        <td id="descriptionArea">
            <ul>
	<li><b>User Story:</b> <em>As a Student, I want to see a preview of my selected images and be warned if my file type is incorrect before I click submit.</em></li>
	<li><b>Technical Scope:</b> Implement <tt>URL.createObjectURL()</tt> for instant image previews. Create a validation utility to check file extensions against the permitted list (<tt>.docx</tt>, <tt>.jpg</tt>, <tt>.png</tt>).</li>
	<li><b>Acceptance Criteria:</b> Users can "delete" a selected file from the preview list before final submission. An error message appears if a user selects a <tt>.pdf</tt> or other forbidden format.</li>
</ul>

            <br/>
        </td>
    </tr>
    </table>

