    <table cellpadding="2" cellspacing="0" border="0" width="100%" align="center">
    <tr>
        <td bgcolor="#bbbbbb" width="1%" nowrap align="center">
            &nbsp;<font color="#ffffff"><b>Description</b></font>&nbsp;
        </td>
        <td>&nbsp;</td>
    </tr>
    </table>

    <table cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" border="0" width="100%">
    <tr>
        <td id="descriptionArea">
            <ul>
	<li><b>User Story:</b> <em>As a Developer, I want a robust mutation hook to handle file uploads so that the UI can reflect real-time progress and handle network timeouts gracefully.</em></li>
	<li><b>Technical Scope:</b> Use <tt>useMutation</tt> from TanStack Query. Implement logic to append files to a <tt>FormData</tt> object. Handle the <tt>onUploadProgress</tt> callback from Axios to feed a progress bar.</li>
	<li><b>Acceptance Criteria:</b> The UI displays a percentage loader during upload. If the server returns an error (e.g., file too large), the mutation triggers a Shadcn "Toast" notification.</li>
</ul>

            <br/>
        </td>
    </tr>
    </table>

